TheEye

TheEye is a test based approach to monitoring. Write any TAP based tests
and put them in a directory and run TheEye against it. It will generate
some nice RRDs for you and creates some stats on the way. This is still
very early stages but the base TAP parsing and stas gathering is done.

If you want to track the progress more closely have a look at
http://github.com/norbu09 for a list of modules that go with this
project.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc TheEye

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=TheEye

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/TheEye

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/TheEye

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/TheEye/


